COMMUNICATIONS and Digital Technologies Minister Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams has been hacked! Her department released a statement earlier today that her WhatsApp has been hacked and that the matter was being investigated. The Twitter post by her department said the hack has resulted “in private and confidential information being in the hands of a third party”.  Minister Ndabeni-Abrahams WhatsApp account HACKED!!! The WhatsApp account of Minister of Communications and Digital Technologies, Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams has been hacked, resulting in private and confidential information being in the hands of a third party.  No other information has been disclosed, especially about the leaked information. Minister Ndabeni-Abrahams also posted on her personal Facebook page informing her friends of the hack. “Friends my WhatsApp is hacked please ignore any communication from me”,her post read.  In February this year, it was revealed that the cellphones of state security minister Ayanda Dlodlo, her deputy and several officials from the State Security Agency (SSA) had been cloned.